properties.sfomuseum:description: Stock certificate issued to B. (Basil) L. Rowe for 20 shares of Pan American Airways Corporation; certificate number O 4186, dated June 28, 1934; orange and white; engraved corporate seal and signatures of H. Preston Morris, Secretary, and J. T. Trippe, President; signed on reverse by Rowe on June 29, 1934; countersigned by The Chase National Bank of the City of New York, registered June 28, 1934 by The New York Trust Company; certificate note by Quayle & Son, New York; document defaced by hole punch cancellation at lower left and right.
